docs {
  # CaterCow Partner Integration Tests

  Tests the partner order API at `/api/partners/*` using CaterCow's
  credentials (`partner: catercow` + `x-api-key`).

  Both `/api/partners/*` and `/api/cater-valley/*` are wired to the
  same handler — these tests use the canonical `/api/partners/*` URL
  advertised in `docs/catercow/API_CONTRACT.md`.

  ## Setup

  Set in your environment file (Development / Production):
    - `PARTNERS_URL` — base partner-API URL (e.g. https://development.readysetllc.com/api/partners)
    - `CATERCOW_PARTNER` — should be `catercow`
    - `CATERCOW_API_KEY` — issued by Ready Set, stored in 1Password

  The CaterCow staging key is generated by:
    `pnpm tsx scripts/seed-catercow-partner.ts` (run against staging DB)

  ## Test Scenarios

  1. Draft order with valid credentials → expect CC- prefix
  2. Update order
  3. Confirm order
  4. Auth failure cases (wrong key, wrong slug, missing headers)
}
